args: All right! I've got about half the firewood\nchopped now, so I think I'll take a break.
I can't believe I'm actually going\non a date with my master.
I wonder what it'll be like...?
＂Should we hold hands? It wouldn't do\nfor us to become separated.＂
Ooo, the night view is lovely!
＂Not nearly so lovely as you,\nmy sweet darling sweetie.＂
*gasp* No! Nononono! We're just going\nshopping—it is definitely NOT a date!
Get your head out of weirdville, Melody!\nFocus! Chop that firewood!
Ooof... I chopped too much...\nEverything hurts and I wanna pass out...
(What is WITH you today, you dorkus?\nYou're just going out with your master\non a shopping trip! Not a date!)
(We'll meet up, walk the town together,\ndo some shopping...)
Hrghrghr... Blargh. Can't sleep at all.
Well, since I'm up, I might as well\ndraw up a plan for our outing!
We're meeting at the castle gates in the\nmorning, right? So when we get to town,\nwe probably go right to the jewelry store.

We'll pop into a few places, and then I'll
give him his present in the town square.
Hmm... I need to nail that present down.
Maybe a handmade sweater?
Yes! That is delightfully doable!\nSo then after the gift, we'll pass\nthe time talking on a little bench...
And I'll finish by giving him a treat here!
This is the perfect date plan.
EXCEPT THAT IT'S NOT A DATE, DORKUS!
What's with all the yelling in here?
Are you all right? Did you fall\nand hurt yourself again?
Yes, you're going to awaken the entire\ncastle if you continue on at this rate.
Philia! Cibella! Wh-what a\ncoincidence seeing you here!
What's that behind your back? A note?
WHAT NO NOTHING IS BEHIND MY BACK\nWHY ARE YOU EVEN ASKING THAT\nYOU'RE WEIRD DON'T BE WEIRD!
Look, did you mess something up again?\nWe won't tell Cleo, so just come clean.
Actually, I DIDN'T mess anything up...
She actually ran away in a cloud of dust.\nI didn't know people could do that.
Alas, she dropped the note in her haste.
Gosh, how much of a klutz do you have to\nbe to try SO hard to hide something and\nthen just drop it while you run off?
The first line is crossed out, but it clearly\nsays ＂Plan For My Date With Master.＂
*pant* I think this is far enough...\nThey shouldn't come after...
DON'T ＂PHILIA＂ ME, HUSSY!\nYOU'RE TRYING TO CUT IN ON MY MAN!
Man? Wh-what man? I don't have\na clue what you're—
THIS! This paper! This...DATE PLAN!\nYou're going on a date with the prince!
HOW COULD YOU DO THIS TO ME?!\nYOU SCARLET WOMAN! YOU FLOOZY!
*pant* I finally...caught up to you...\nPhilia! Calm yourself.
Melody, please explain. How long have\nyou and the prince been engaged in a... \nWell, a dating type of relationship?
It's not a DATE date, you guys!\nIt's just...you know. A ＂date.＂\nLike, a day we spend together.
I just wanted to show my master\nhow much I appreciate him.
Okay, so here's the whole deal...

I see. So basically, you're simply going
shopping in your capacity as a maid,
and thought you'd take the opportunity to
show your gratitude while you were at it.
Pretty much, yeah. See, I was a maid in\na lot of places before this, and I ended\nup being fired every single time.
I mean, who WOULDN'T fire a big ol'\nklutz like me, am I right?
But my master is different. He said I'm\nbright and cheerful, and that having\nme around is good for morale.
I've never known the warmth of a family,\nbut he told me I could think of everyone\nin the castle as my own.
I became a maid because I wanted to\nexperience a familial bond, so that\nmade me truly, genuinely happy.
And that's why I want to thank him.\nNo, why I NEED to.
Okay, I get it. Er, and sorry about\nthat whole ＂floozy＂ thing.
It sounds like things were pretty tough for\nyou, so I get why you want to thank him.
And while I'm still concerned about the \ntwo of you going out...I'll support you.
Perhaps you might let me help\nin this endeavor as well?
Of COURSE you can help, Cibella!\nThis is going to be the best date ever!
Except it's NOT A DATE, DORKUS! Sheesh!
So this really IS just a day trip, right?\nNot a date?
